{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Evan Abraham | image = | fullname = | birth_date = 1899 | birth_place = [[Swansea]], Wales | death_date = | position = Outside-left | years1 = 1922–1925 | clubs1=[[Merthyr Town F.C.|Merthyr Town]] | caps1=57 | goals1 = 1 | years2 = 1926 | clubs2=[[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] | caps2=13 | goals2 = 0 }} '''Evan Abraham''' (born 1899, date of death unknown) was a [[association football|footballer]] who played in the [[Football League]] for [[Merthyr Town F.C.|Merthyr Town]] and [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]]. He was born in [[Swansea]], Wales.<ref>{{cite book|author=Michael Joyce|title=The Football League player's records 1888 to 1939|ISBN=1899468676}}</ref>
