The '''NVIDIA Deep Learning Accelerator''' (NVDLA) is an [[open source]] [[neural network]] accelerator created by [[NVIDIA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/moorinsights/2018/03/29/arm-chooses-nvidia-open-source-ai-chip-technology/|title=Arm Chooses NVIDIA Open-Source CNN AI Chip Technology|last=Freund|first=Karl|date=March 29, 2018|work=Forbes|publisher=Moor Insights and Strategy|accessdate=June 13, 2018}}</ref> The accelerator is written in [[verilog]] and is configurable and scalable to meet many different architecture needs. NVDLA is merely an accelerator and any process must be scheduled and arbitered by an outside entity such as a CPU.<ref>http://nvdla.org/primer.html</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://arxiv.org/pdf/1805.02566.pdf|title=  MAESTRO: An Open-source Infrastructure for Modeling Dataflows within Deep Learning Accelerators
