{{Infobox football biography | name = Sterică Adamache |image=Stere Adamache.jpg |image_size=240px | fullname = <!-- if different --> | birth_date = 17 August 1941 | birth_place = [[Galaţi]], [[Romania]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1978|07|09|1941|08|17|df=y}} | death_place = [[Crișan, Tulcea|Crişan]], Romania | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1960&ndash;1962 | years2 = 1962&ndash;1963 | years3 = 1963&ndash;1977 | clubs1 = Dinamo Galaţi | clubs2 = Viitorul Bucureşti | clubs3 = [[FC Brașov|Steagul Roşu Braşov]] | caps1 = ? | caps2 = 5 | caps3 = 248 | goals1 = 0 | goals2 = 0 | goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 1970&ndash;1972 | nationalteam1 = [[Romania national football team|Romania]] | nationalcaps1 = 7 | nationalgoals1 = 0 }}
'''Stere "Sterică" Adamache''' (17 August 1941 – 9 July 1978) was a Romanian football goalkeeper. He played at the 1970 World Cup in the match between Romania and Brazil. He conceded two goals, one of them from [[Pelé]], and was substituted with [[Necula Răducanu|Rică Răducanu]]. He drowned in the [[Danube]] in 1978.
