'''Wilhelm Adolf''' was a [[Germany|German]] [[luge]]r who competed in the late 1920s. He won a gold medal in the men's doubles event at the [[FIL European Luge Championships 1928|1928 European championships]] in [[Schreiberhau]], [[Germany]] (now [[Szklarska Poręba]], [[Poland]]).<ref>{{cite web|title=List of European luge champions|url=http://www.eiskanal.com/eiskanal-kunstbahnrennrodeln-europameisterschaften.html|website=Eiskanal|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080325014953/http://www.eiskanal.com/eiskanal-kunstbahnrennrodeln-europameisterschaften.html|archivedate=2008-03-25|accessdate=2015-02-08|deadurl=yes|language=de}}</ref>

